00:00:02.856 --> 00:00:05.240 align:middle line:90%


00:00:05.240 --> 00:00:10.260 align:middle line:84%
>> Thinking Allowed
conversations on the leading

00:00:10.260 --> 00:00:14.640 align:middle line:84%
edge of knowledge and discovery
with psychologist Jeffrey

00:00:14.640 --> 00:00:15.756 align:middle line:90%
Mishlove.

00:00:15.756 --> 00:00:18.186 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:18.186 --> 00:00:31.800 align:middle line:90%


00:00:31.800 --> 00:00:32.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Hello and welcome.

00:00:32.710 --> 00:00:33.760 align:middle line:90%
I'm Jeffrey Mishlove.

00:00:33.760 --> 00:00:37.350 align:middle line:84%
Today we're going to explore
the mystery of consciousness.

00:00:37.350 --> 00:00:39.720 align:middle line:84%
My guest is Peter
Russell, a fellow

00:00:39.720 --> 00:00:42.630 align:middle line:84%
of the Institute of Noetic
Sciences in Sausalito,

00:00:42.630 --> 00:00:43.770 align:middle line:90%
California.

00:00:43.770 --> 00:00:47.280 align:middle line:84%
Peter has written numerous
books, including the TM book,

00:00:47.280 --> 00:00:51.270 align:middle line:84%
"The Brain Book," a
translation of the Upanishads,

00:00:51.270 --> 00:00:56.460 align:middle line:84%
"Waking Up in Time," "The
Global Brain," and "From Science

00:00:56.460 --> 00:00:57.840 align:middle line:90%
to God."

00:00:57.840 --> 00:00:58.800 align:middle line:90%
Welcome, Peter.

00:00:58.800 --> 00:00:59.310 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

00:00:59.310 --> 00:01:00.477 align:middle line:90%
Lovely to be with you today.

00:01:00.477 --> 00:01:02.490 align:middle line:84%
>> It's a pleasure
to be with you.

00:01:02.490 --> 00:01:04.860 align:middle line:84%
We seem to be living
in a culture that

00:01:04.860 --> 00:01:10.080 align:middle line:84%
has some very schizophrenic
ideas about consciousness.

00:01:10.080 --> 00:01:13.250 align:middle line:84%
Mainstream science
today is just,

00:01:13.250 --> 00:01:17.670 align:middle line:84%
I think, starting to accept
the notion that consciousness

00:01:17.670 --> 00:01:19.860 align:middle line:84%
is something they ought
to begin to deal with.

00:01:19.860 --> 00:01:23.130 align:middle line:10%
>> Yes, I think consciousness
is the great problem

00:01:23.130 --> 00:01:25.060 align:middle line:10%
for the scientific culture.

00:01:25.060 --> 00:01:25.860 align:middle line:10%
It's fascinating.

00:01:25.860 --> 00:01:27.930 align:middle line:10%
It's the one thing
we cannot deny.

00:01:27.930 --> 00:01:29.910 align:middle line:10%
Each and every one of
us is a conscious being.

00:01:29.910 --> 00:01:32.970 align:middle line:10%
We have inner
experiences all the time.

00:01:32.970 --> 00:01:35.290 align:middle line:10%
Every scientist is
a conscious being.

00:01:35.290 --> 00:01:38.370 align:middle line:10%
The one thing that science
cannot explain is how

00:01:38.370 --> 00:01:39.820 align:middle line:10%
consciousness arises.

00:01:39.820 --> 00:01:40.620 align:middle line:10%
And you're right.

00:01:40.620 --> 00:01:42.203 align:middle line:10%
At the moment, there's
a lot of people

00:01:42.203 --> 00:01:43.500 align:middle line:10%
beginning to look at that.

00:01:43.500 --> 00:01:44.840 align:middle line:84%
But I think they're
probably on the wrong track.

00:01:44.840 --> 00:01:46.965 align:middle line:84%
They're beginning to look
at how it might arise out

00:01:46.965 --> 00:01:50.310 align:middle line:84%
of physics, out of quantum
theory, these sorts of things.

00:01:50.310 --> 00:01:53.280 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, for
virtually a century,

00:01:53.280 --> 00:01:56.730 align:middle line:84%
it seemed as if science simply
tried to deny that there was

00:01:56.730 --> 00:01:59.130 align:middle line:90%
even a problem there at all.

00:01:59.130 --> 00:02:00.030 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:02:00.030 --> 00:02:01.620 align:middle line:84%
I think this always
happens with problems.

00:02:01.620 --> 00:02:03.120 align:middle line:84%
It's what Thomas
Kuhn showed when he

00:02:03.120 --> 00:02:04.350 align:middle line:90%
talked about paradigm shifts.

00:02:04.350 --> 00:02:05.725 align:middle line:84%
And what happens
at the beginning

00:02:05.725 --> 00:02:07.703 align:middle line:90%
is science ignores the problem.

00:02:07.703 --> 00:02:09.120 align:middle line:84%
And they did that
for a long time.

00:02:09.120 --> 00:02:10.912 align:middle line:84%
We don't have to worry
about consciousness.

00:02:10.912 --> 00:02:14.760 align:middle line:84%
Partly modern science seems
to understand the functioning

00:02:14.760 --> 00:02:18.000 align:middle line:84%
of the material world perfectly
well without any need to go

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:21.210 align:middle line:84%
into consciousness, until
it comes to the fact that we

00:02:21.210 --> 00:02:24.870 align:middle line:84%
cannot explain at all
why we have awareness.

00:02:24.870 --> 00:02:27.780 align:middle line:84%
It's actually easier
to explain the Big Bang

00:02:27.780 --> 00:02:30.510 align:middle line:84%
and how elements evolved
into atoms and atoms evolved

00:02:30.510 --> 00:02:33.030 align:middle line:84%
into molecules, which
became simple systems, which

00:02:33.030 --> 00:02:35.250 align:middle line:84%
evolved into human
beings like ourselves.

00:02:35.250 --> 00:02:39.150 align:middle line:84%
That is easier to understand
than why any one of us

00:02:39.150 --> 00:02:41.130 align:middle line:90%
ever has a single thought.

00:02:41.130 --> 00:02:44.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, it strikes me, Peter,
that the problem runs even

00:02:44.710 --> 00:02:45.510 align:middle line:90%
deeper.

00:02:45.510 --> 00:02:48.450 align:middle line:84%
Because many cultures in
other historical periods

00:02:48.450 --> 00:02:50.540 align:middle line:84%
didn't have this problem
with consciousness.

00:02:50.540 --> 00:02:53.290 align:middle line:84%
It's unique, I think,
to Western culture,

00:02:53.290 --> 00:02:56.250 align:middle line:84%
and particularly in the
19th and 20th centuries.

00:02:56.250 --> 00:03:00.720 align:middle line:84%
It strikes me that the
20th century certainly

00:03:00.720 --> 00:03:04.830 align:middle line:84%
was the bloodiest century in
human history, a dark century--

00:03:04.830 --> 00:03:08.280 align:middle line:84%
two world wars,
many massive periods

00:03:08.280 --> 00:03:11.340 align:middle line:84%
of starvation, social
alienation, and revolution.

00:03:11.340 --> 00:03:15.750 align:middle line:84%
And I tend to think that
that sort of social darkness

00:03:15.750 --> 00:03:20.130 align:middle line:84%
is not unrelated to
the fact that we lived

00:03:20.130 --> 00:03:22.950 align:middle line:84%
during that century in an
era in which consciousness

00:03:22.950 --> 00:03:28.140 align:middle line:84%
itself wasn't even recognized
by the major social institution

00:03:28.140 --> 00:03:29.620 align:middle line:90%
of inquiry, being science.

00:03:29.620 --> 00:03:30.420 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:03:30.420 --> 00:03:33.030 align:middle line:84%
Science just didn't want
to look at it at all.

00:03:33.030 --> 00:03:34.650 align:middle line:84%
But I think now it
is being forced to,

00:03:34.650 --> 00:03:36.400 align:middle line:84%
and I think several
things are forcing it.

00:03:36.400 --> 00:03:39.240 align:middle line:84%
One, there's things in physics
like in quantum physics

00:03:39.240 --> 00:03:41.160 align:middle line:84%
and relativity
where consciousness

00:03:41.160 --> 00:03:44.610 align:middle line:84%
seems to play a part
in what we observe.

00:03:44.610 --> 00:03:47.310 align:middle line:84%
And now in terms of our
brain, understanding

00:03:47.310 --> 00:03:51.030 align:middle line:84%
of the brain, which is probably
one of the fastest growing

00:03:51.030 --> 00:03:53.737 align:middle line:84%
areas of science,
we're coming up

00:03:53.737 --> 00:03:55.320 align:middle line:84%
against the question
of consciousness.

00:03:55.320 --> 00:03:57.830 align:middle line:84%
We can understand so much
now about the human brain.

00:03:57.830 --> 00:03:59.280 align:middle line:90%
There's still a lot more to go.

00:03:59.280 --> 00:04:02.250 align:middle line:84%
But that raises the question
of what is consciousness?

00:04:02.250 --> 00:04:04.320 align:middle line:84%
And how does
consciousness emerge?

00:04:04.320 --> 00:04:07.770 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, philosophers such as
David Chalmers talk about it

00:04:07.770 --> 00:04:13.870 align:middle line:84%
as the hard problem, that you
can't get from here to there.

00:04:13.870 --> 00:04:19.079 align:middle line:84%
From a materialistic worldview,
you simply cannot arrive at any

00:04:19.079 --> 00:04:22.860 align:middle line:84%
sort of mechanism which is
required by materialism that

00:04:22.860 --> 00:04:24.160 align:middle line:90%
will lead you to consciousness.

00:04:24.160 --> 00:04:24.960 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly.

00:04:24.960 --> 00:04:26.970 align:middle line:84%
The two are totally
different types.

00:04:26.970 --> 00:04:30.960 align:middle line:84%
The material world, we assume,
is unconscious and material.

00:04:30.960 --> 00:04:33.435 align:middle line:84%
Consciousness is
immaterial and conscious.

00:04:33.435 --> 00:04:36.270 align:middle line:84%
So how does something as
immaterial as consciousness

00:04:36.270 --> 00:04:39.280 align:middle line:84%
ever arise from something
as unconscious as matter?

00:04:39.280 --> 00:04:41.280 align:middle line:90%
That's the hard problem.

00:04:41.280 --> 00:04:43.860 align:middle line:84%
But I think it's, in a
way, the question is wrong.

00:04:43.860 --> 00:04:47.340 align:middle line:84%
We are assuming that the
real world is the material

00:04:47.340 --> 00:04:49.350 align:middle line:90%
world of spacetime and matter.

00:04:49.350 --> 00:04:51.570 align:middle line:84%
And that's the problem, I
think, that modern science

00:04:51.570 --> 00:04:53.330 align:middle line:84%
has got stuck in
this worldview that

00:04:53.330 --> 00:04:54.810 align:middle line:90%
says that is the real world.

00:04:54.810 --> 00:04:57.420 align:middle line:84%
And then we are posed with
the question, well then,

00:04:57.420 --> 00:04:59.140 align:middle line:84%
how does consciousness
arise from it?

00:04:59.140 --> 00:05:00.510 align:middle line:90%
I don't think it does.

00:05:00.510 --> 00:05:02.270 align:middle line:90%
My view is consciousness is--

00:05:02.270 --> 00:05:06.450 align:middle line:84%
>> If we let go of that
metaphysical assumption made

00:05:06.450 --> 00:05:10.080 align:middle line:84%
by materialistic science, the
problem of consciousness no

00:05:10.080 --> 00:05:11.850 align:middle line:84%
longer seems like
such a problem.

00:05:11.850 --> 00:05:14.610 align:middle line:84%
It becomes a first
cause, a principle.

00:05:14.610 --> 00:05:17.280 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, yes, which is what
a lot of the great spiritual

00:05:17.280 --> 00:05:19.380 align:middle line:84%
traditions and philosophers
have said all along,

00:05:19.380 --> 00:05:22.290 align:middle line:84%
is that consciousness is,
and it's a primary quality

00:05:22.290 --> 00:05:23.970 align:middle line:90%
of the universe.

00:05:23.970 --> 00:05:26.610 align:middle line:84%
>> On the other
hand, in science,

00:05:26.610 --> 00:05:31.300 align:middle line:84%
there is an effort to describe
how consciousness would evolve

00:05:31.300 --> 00:05:36.558 align:middle line:84%
from neurobiology, how computer
models might have something

00:05:36.558 --> 00:05:37.600 align:middle line:90%
to do with consciousness.

00:05:37.600 --> 00:05:42.730 align:middle line:84%
After all, memory seems to be
a property of computer systems.

00:05:42.730 --> 00:05:45.550 align:middle line:84%
Perception is a
property of neurons.

00:05:45.550 --> 00:05:47.830 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, I'm not so sure it is.

00:05:47.830 --> 00:05:49.760 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, let me say sensation.

00:05:49.760 --> 00:05:53.420 align:middle line:84%
>> They are clearly involved
in mediating the process.

00:05:53.420 --> 00:05:55.780 align:middle line:84%
And I think it comes back
to saying that if we believe

00:05:55.780 --> 00:05:57.880 align:middle line:84%
the material world is
real, then we think

00:05:57.880 --> 00:05:59.670 align:middle line:90%
that they are the cause of it.

00:05:59.670 --> 00:06:01.420 align:middle line:84%
But I think they're
part of the mediation.

00:06:01.420 --> 00:06:03.970 align:middle line:84%
I don't think they
actually create experience.

00:06:03.970 --> 00:06:06.520 align:middle line:84%
I don't think neurons
create consciousness.

00:06:06.520 --> 00:06:09.980 align:middle line:84%
They may be amplifiers
of what is going on,

00:06:09.980 --> 00:06:13.930 align:middle line:84%
and they may help create the
details of our experience.

00:06:13.930 --> 00:06:16.690 align:middle line:84%
But I don't think they
create experience itself.

00:06:16.690 --> 00:06:19.300 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, David Chalmers
sometimes talks about--

00:06:19.300 --> 00:06:22.930 align:middle line:84%
he's a professor,
studies consciousness.

00:06:22.930 --> 00:06:25.430 align:middle line:84%
We've interviewed him, the
University of California Santa

00:06:25.430 --> 00:06:26.230 align:middle line:90%
Cruz.

00:06:26.230 --> 00:06:28.920 align:middle line:84%
He suggests there are the easy
problems and the hard problems.

00:06:28.920 --> 00:06:29.720 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:06:29.720 --> 00:06:33.880 align:middle line:84%
>> The easy problems might
be, how is it that when I see,

00:06:33.880 --> 00:06:38.540 align:middle line:84%
I see you and not just a bunch
of patches of light and forum,

00:06:38.540 --> 00:06:40.840 align:middle line:84%
that there is a
coherence to my vision?

00:06:40.840 --> 00:06:43.050 align:middle line:84%
That's a problem,
perhaps, for neurology.

00:06:43.050 --> 00:06:43.850 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:06:43.850 --> 00:06:45.370 align:middle line:10%
And these are all
the easy problems.

00:06:45.370 --> 00:06:46.350 align:middle line:10%
How does memory work?

00:06:46.350 --> 00:06:47.570 align:middle line:10%
How does perception work?

00:06:47.570 --> 00:06:49.120 align:middle line:10%
How do we control the body?

00:06:49.120 --> 00:06:50.440 align:middle line:10%
How do thoughts arise?

00:06:50.440 --> 00:06:53.200 align:middle line:10%
The easy problems are
to do with understanding

00:06:53.200 --> 00:06:54.282 align:middle line:10%
the neurophysiology.

00:06:54.282 --> 00:06:55.990 align:middle line:10%
They're called easy,
but they're probably

00:06:55.990 --> 00:06:57.850 align:middle line:10%
the most difficult
problems we've faced.

00:06:57.850 --> 00:06:58.650 align:middle line:10%
>> Yes.

00:06:58.650 --> 00:07:01.960 align:middle line:84%
>> But the point is, ultimately
we may be able to understand

00:07:01.960 --> 00:07:02.810 align:middle line:90%
those easy problems.

00:07:02.810 --> 00:07:06.220 align:middle line:84%
We may be able to understand
how the brain analyzes

00:07:06.220 --> 00:07:09.040 align:middle line:84%
a visual scene in front of
us and reconstitutes that

00:07:09.040 --> 00:07:10.810 align:middle line:90%
into a picture.

00:07:10.810 --> 00:07:14.080 align:middle line:84%
But the hard problem is even
when we understand all of that,

00:07:14.080 --> 00:07:17.710 align:middle line:84%
why should any of that
processing in the brain ever

00:07:17.710 --> 00:07:20.200 align:middle line:84%
give rise to a
subjective experience?

00:07:20.200 --> 00:07:22.420 align:middle line:84%
Why does it all
go on in the dark?

00:07:22.420 --> 00:07:24.290 align:middle line:90%
That's the hard problem.

00:07:24.290 --> 00:07:26.830 align:middle line:84%
And to me, that's pointing
towards something fundamentally

00:07:26.830 --> 00:07:29.200 align:middle line:84%
wrong with the current
scientific worldview.

00:07:29.200 --> 00:07:30.680 align:middle line:84%
And yet scientists
don't see that.

00:07:30.680 --> 00:07:32.973 align:middle line:84%
They keep on trying
to explain that

00:07:32.973 --> 00:07:34.640 align:middle line:84%
within the current
scientific worldview.

00:07:34.640 --> 00:07:37.450 align:middle line:84%
So some people like
Hameroff believe

00:07:37.450 --> 00:07:39.460 align:middle line:84%
it's to do with
tiny microtubules

00:07:39.460 --> 00:07:43.123 align:middle line:84%
in the brain cells, which you
can get coherent functions

00:07:43.123 --> 00:07:45.040 align:middle line:84%
happening there, laser
like effects with water

00:07:45.040 --> 00:07:47.830 align:middle line:84%
molecules, which
he suggests maybe

00:07:47.830 --> 00:07:49.255 align:middle line:90%
is the source of consciousness.

00:07:49.255 --> 00:07:51.130 align:middle line:84%
But you're still faced
with the hard problem,

00:07:51.130 --> 00:07:54.820 align:middle line:84%
how does a quantum process
give rise to something

00:07:54.820 --> 00:07:57.640 align:middle line:84%
as subjective as
our own experience?

00:07:57.640 --> 00:08:00.460 align:middle line:84%
And the greatest twist
in this whole paradox

00:08:00.460 --> 00:08:03.790 align:middle line:84%
is that in the end, all we
ever know is consciousness.

00:08:03.790 --> 00:08:06.257 align:middle line:84%
We don't actually know
the world of matter.

00:08:06.257 --> 00:08:07.840 align:middle line:84%
I mean, right now,
we're sitting here.

00:08:07.840 --> 00:08:09.465 align:middle line:84%
We're experiencing
the world around us.

00:08:09.465 --> 00:08:11.380 align:middle line:10%
This table seems very real.

00:08:11.380 --> 00:08:14.740 align:middle line:10%
But all I'm actually
knowing is the re-creation

00:08:14.740 --> 00:08:18.100 align:middle line:10%
in my consciousness, in
my mind, of this table

00:08:18.100 --> 00:08:19.720 align:middle line:10%
with its color
and its solidness,

00:08:19.720 --> 00:08:21.610 align:middle line:10%
and I'm hearing the
sound of your voice.

00:08:21.610 --> 00:08:24.600 align:middle line:10%
But all of that is a
creation in consciousness.

00:08:24.600 --> 00:08:26.100 align:middle line:10%
>> A simulation, so to speak.

00:08:26.100 --> 00:08:28.540 align:middle line:10%
>> Yes, it's all a
simulation of the world.

00:08:28.540 --> 00:08:30.940 align:middle line:10%
>> And the simulation
is obviously conditioned

00:08:30.940 --> 00:08:32.840 align:middle line:10%
by our apparatus.

00:08:32.840 --> 00:08:33.640 align:middle line:10%
>> Yeah.

00:08:33.640 --> 00:08:35.750 align:middle line:10%
But what I'm saying
is in the end,

00:08:35.750 --> 00:08:37.870 align:middle line:10%
the only thing we know
for certain is actually

00:08:37.870 --> 00:08:39.490 align:middle line:10%
consciousness.

00:08:39.490 --> 00:08:42.039 align:middle line:84%
The world of spacetime
and matter is secondary.

00:08:42.039 --> 00:08:43.659 align:middle line:90%
We know it through inference.

00:08:43.659 --> 00:08:45.790 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, that's a very
interesting point.

00:08:45.790 --> 00:08:50.620 align:middle line:84%
And it's quite contrary to the
basic axioms of empiricism,

00:08:50.620 --> 00:08:54.578 align:middle line:84%
which suggests that the
material world is primary

00:08:54.578 --> 00:08:55.870 align:middle line:90%
and consciousness is secondary.

00:08:55.870 --> 00:08:59.800 align:middle line:84%
>> Exactly, and that's the shift
that I think we have to reverse

00:08:59.800 --> 00:09:00.880 align:middle line:90%
that whole polarity.

00:09:00.880 --> 00:09:04.503 align:middle line:84%
>> William James developed what
he called radical empiricism,

00:09:04.503 --> 00:09:05.670 align:middle line:90%
in which he made that point.

00:09:05.670 --> 00:09:07.420 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, he was stepping
in that direction,

00:09:07.420 --> 00:09:09.430 align:middle line:84%
that we need to really
trust our experience.

00:09:09.430 --> 00:09:12.460 align:middle line:84%
Because the fundamental
datum is experience.

00:09:12.460 --> 00:09:14.950 align:middle line:84%
And experience takes
place in consciousness.

00:09:14.950 --> 00:09:17.320 align:middle line:84%
>> I should mention for
the benefit of our viewers,

00:09:17.320 --> 00:09:21.500 align:middle line:84%
William James is considered the
founder of American psychology

00:09:21.500 --> 00:09:23.380 align:middle line:90%
and lived around a century ago.

00:09:23.380 --> 00:09:26.940 align:middle line:84%
But many great thinkers
have made the same point.

00:09:26.940 --> 00:09:29.280 align:middle line:84%
Sir Arthur Eddington
in physics--

00:09:29.280 --> 00:09:30.540 align:middle line:90%
>> Yep.

00:09:30.540 --> 00:09:32.410 align:middle line:90%
I think and many physicists.

00:09:32.410 --> 00:09:34.580 align:middle line:84%
For example, Schrodinger,
we have Schrodinger's wave

00:09:34.580 --> 00:09:35.380 align:middle line:90%
equation.

00:09:35.380 --> 00:09:36.330 align:middle line:90%
>> Erwin Schrodinger.

00:09:36.330 --> 00:09:38.205 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, one of the
great quantum physicists.

00:09:38.205 --> 00:09:41.680 align:middle line:84%
He was saying in the end,
the ultimate reality is mind.

00:09:41.680 --> 00:09:44.110 align:middle line:84%
And he came to that
conclusion as a physicist.

00:09:44.110 --> 00:09:45.550 align:middle line:90%
The ultimate reality is mind.

00:09:45.550 --> 00:09:49.510 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, it seems to me that
many people suggest since we

00:09:49.510 --> 00:09:54.880 align:middle line:84%
can't seem to even conceivably
derive consciousness from

00:09:54.880 --> 00:09:58.370 align:middle line:84%
physical systems, maybe
consciousness is primary.

00:09:58.370 --> 00:09:59.170 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:09:59.170 --> 00:10:02.110 align:middle line:10%
Well, that's what I'm
arguing for in my book.

00:10:02.110 --> 00:10:05.290 align:middle line:10%
If we make consciousness
primary, what is interesting,

00:10:05.290 --> 00:10:08.355 align:middle line:10%
it doesn't change a single
thing in modern science.

00:10:08.355 --> 00:10:09.730 align:middle line:10%
It doesn't change
any of physics.

00:10:09.730 --> 00:10:11.272 align:middle line:10%
It doesn't change
any of mathematics.

00:10:11.272 --> 00:10:12.400 align:middle line:10%
It doesn't change biology.

00:10:12.400 --> 00:10:14.620 align:middle line:10%
All of that is exactly the same.

00:10:14.620 --> 00:10:17.950 align:middle line:10%
But what it does do is
offer some interesting new

00:10:17.950 --> 00:10:19.600 align:middle line:10%
interpretations of
some things which

00:10:19.600 --> 00:10:21.558 align:middle line:10%
are happening in quantum
physics and relativity

00:10:21.558 --> 00:10:23.050 align:middle line:10%
where consciousness
gets involved.

00:10:23.050 --> 00:10:25.960 align:middle line:84%
But it doesn't actually
change the mathematics at all.

00:10:25.960 --> 00:10:29.960 align:middle line:84%
What it does do is open us up
to a whole new understanding

00:10:29.960 --> 00:10:31.892 align:middle line:84%
of spirituality,
and I think what

00:10:31.892 --> 00:10:33.350 align:middle line:84%
all the great
teachers have been on

00:10:33.350 --> 00:10:35.580 align:middle line:90%
about for thousands of years.

00:10:35.580 --> 00:10:38.150 align:middle line:84%
And I think this is
probably why humanity,

00:10:38.150 --> 00:10:40.640 align:middle line:84%
the human race is creating
such havoc when you talk

00:10:40.640 --> 00:10:42.690 align:middle line:84%
about the bloody
wars and things,

00:10:42.690 --> 00:10:46.823 align:middle line:84%
is because we're living in
a spiritually arid time.

00:10:46.823 --> 00:10:47.990 align:middle line:90%
>> We don't know who we are.

00:10:47.990 --> 00:10:50.060 align:middle line:84%
>> We've lost touch with
our spiritual roots,

00:10:50.060 --> 00:10:53.300 align:middle line:84%
and religion is sort of put
right back on the back shelf.

00:10:53.300 --> 00:10:54.800 align:middle line:84%
Some people go to
church on Sundays.

00:10:54.800 --> 00:10:56.700 align:middle line:90%
Most don't even do that.

00:10:56.700 --> 00:10:59.593 align:middle line:84%
So spirituality has dropped
right out of our culture.

00:10:59.593 --> 00:11:01.760 align:middle line:84%
And that, to me, is what
is interesting about making

00:11:01.760 --> 00:11:04.310 align:middle line:84%
this shift in worldview,
is that it actually

00:11:04.310 --> 00:11:08.600 align:middle line:84%
allows spiritual wisdom
to come in and sit side

00:11:08.600 --> 00:11:12.560 align:middle line:84%
by side with the scientific
worldview without any conflict.

00:11:12.560 --> 00:11:14.900 align:middle line:84%
So it's expanding the
worldview so that both

00:11:14.900 --> 00:11:16.490 align:middle line:90%
can sit comfortably together.

