same thing with society.

00:13:01.550 --> 00:13:04.660 align:middle line:84%
The laws that govern society
is an emergent phenomenon

00:13:04.660 --> 00:13:06.040 align:middle line:90%
that have come out of life.

00:13:06.040 --> 00:13:09.070 align:middle line:84%
But they're still laws
of the physical world.

00:13:09.070 --> 00:13:12.590 align:middle line:84%
Consciousness does not
belong to the physical world.

00:13:12.590 --> 00:13:15.820 align:middle line:84%
And so you cannot have something
which is of a totally different

00:13:15.820 --> 00:13:18.672 align:middle line:84%
type emerging from
the material type.

00:13:18.672 --> 00:13:20.380 align:middle line:10%
>> I want to be fair
to the materialists,

00:13:20.380 --> 00:13:24.400 align:middle line:10%
because I know that if there
were such a person in the room,

00:13:24.400 --> 00:13:26.050 align:middle line:10%
he would debate you vigorously--

00:13:26.050 --> 00:13:27.070 align:middle line:10%
>> He may well do.

00:13:27.070 --> 00:13:27.520 align:middle line:10%
>> --on this point--

00:13:27.520 --> 00:13:29.110 align:middle line:10%
>> And I would debate
him vigorously.

00:13:29.110 --> 00:13:29.930 align:middle line:90%
>> --for days.

00:13:29.930 --> 00:13:30.730 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:13:30.730 --> 00:13:32.940 align:middle line:84%
>> And I think that
needs to be pointed out.

00:13:32.940 --> 00:13:36.010 align:middle line:90%
A very, I think, very--

00:13:36.010 --> 00:13:39.700 align:middle line:84%
I want to say strong, but I
will say detailed arguments can

00:13:39.700 --> 00:13:42.700 align:middle line:84%
be made on behalf
of the position

00:13:42.700 --> 00:13:45.730 align:middle line:84%
that consciousness
might just be emergent.

00:13:45.730 --> 00:13:49.720 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, but I think all those
arguments are founded upon

00:13:49.720 --> 00:13:53.163 align:middle line:84%
the assumption that the
spacetime matter world is real.

00:13:53.163 --> 00:13:54.580 align:middle line:84%
And I think that
is the assumption

00:13:54.580 --> 00:13:55.930 align:middle line:90%
we need to challenge.

00:13:55.930 --> 00:13:59.350 align:middle line:84%
I think it's very parallel to
what happened 500 years ago,

00:13:59.350 --> 00:14:02.350 align:middle line:84%
when everybody thought the Earth
was the center of the universe

00:14:02.350 --> 00:14:03.760 align:middle line:90%
and it was still.

00:14:03.760 --> 00:14:05.375 align:middle line:84%
And people like
Copernicus came along

00:14:05.375 --> 00:14:06.740 align:middle line:90%
and suggested the Earth moved.

00:14:06.740 --> 00:14:08.960 align:middle line:84%
And they said,
that is ridiculous.

00:14:08.960 --> 00:14:11.770 align:middle line:84%
There is no evidence
whatsoever the Earth is moving.

00:14:11.770 --> 00:14:14.140 align:middle line:84%
If it was, thing would
fly across the room.

00:14:14.140 --> 00:14:15.820 align:middle line:90%
The Earth is clearly still.

00:14:15.820 --> 00:14:18.743 align:middle line:90%
Don't be so ridiculous.

00:14:18.743 --> 00:14:21.160 align:middle line:84%
Because that was the belief
system everybody was stuck in.

00:14:21.160 --> 00:14:22.290 align:middle line:90%
And I think the same today.

00:14:22.290 --> 00:14:24.550 align:middle line:84%
We are all stuck in
this belief system

00:14:24.550 --> 00:14:26.440 align:middle line:84%
that spacetime and
matter are real.

00:14:26.440 --> 00:14:28.960 align:middle line:84%
And people can argue
very coherently

00:14:28.960 --> 00:14:31.540 align:middle line:84%
about that within
that assumption.

00:14:31.540 --> 00:14:33.250 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, when you
say we're all stuck,

00:14:33.250 --> 00:14:36.530 align:middle line:84%
what you really mean are people
who subscribe to scientific

00:14:36.530 --> 00:14:37.330 align:middle line:90%
materialism.

00:14:37.330 --> 00:14:38.130 align:middle line:90%
>> OK, yes.

00:14:38.130 --> 00:14:39.760 align:middle line:84%
>> That's actually,
I would estimate,

00:14:39.760 --> 00:14:43.520 align:middle line:84%
even in the Western world
maybe 25% of the populations.

00:14:43.520 --> 00:14:44.320 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:14:44.320 --> 00:14:46.320 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what the
actual percentage is, yes.

00:14:46.320 --> 00:14:49.240 align:middle line:84%
When I say we all, I should
rephrase that more accurately,

00:14:49.240 --> 00:14:52.000 align:middle line:84%
most scientists, the
majority of scientists.

00:14:52.000 --> 00:14:55.470 align:middle line:84%
>> Other people tend to
have a religious worldview

00:14:55.470 --> 00:14:58.660 align:middle line:84%
or a philosophical worldview
that is larger than just

00:14:58.660 --> 00:14:59.860 align:middle line:90%
scientific materialism.

00:14:59.860 --> 00:15:00.670 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:15:00.670 --> 00:15:02.290 align:middle line:84%
And yet scientific
materialism seems

00:15:02.290 --> 00:15:05.230 align:middle line:84%
to be the worldview by
which our culture operates,

00:15:05.230 --> 00:15:07.870 align:middle line:84%
which our political institutions
and legal institutes,

00:15:07.870 --> 00:15:10.168 align:middle line:84%
everything works
on that assumption.

00:15:10.168 --> 00:15:11.710 align:middle line:84%
Although, as you
say, a lot of people

00:15:11.710 --> 00:15:13.690 align:middle line:84%
don't actually agree
with that underneath.

00:15:13.690 --> 00:15:14.490 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:15:14.490 --> 00:15:18.790 align:middle line:84%
In fact, even our legal
system believes very firmly

00:15:18.790 --> 00:15:21.520 align:middle line:84%
in free will and
human choice, which

00:15:21.520 --> 00:15:23.960 align:middle line:84%
total scientific materialism
doesn't allow for.

00:15:23.960 --> 00:15:24.760 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:15:24.760 --> 00:15:26.218 align:middle line:84%
Well, that's a
strange one when you

00:15:26.218 --> 00:15:30.260 align:middle line:84%
get scientists who choose
not to believe in free will.

00:15:30.260 --> 00:15:35.140 align:middle line:84%
>> So there are very venerable
structures in our society that

00:15:35.140 --> 00:15:39.940 align:middle line:84%
hold a view of consciousness
that's quite different from

00:15:39.940 --> 00:15:41.270 align:middle line:90%
the view of science.

00:15:41.270 --> 00:15:44.140 align:middle line:84%
In fact, most people think
it odd to believe that we

00:15:44.140 --> 00:15:45.890 align:middle line:90%
have no free will at all.

00:15:45.890 --> 00:15:46.690 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:15:46.690 --> 00:15:48.640 align:middle line:84%
But that's why, you see,
I think consciousness

00:15:48.640 --> 00:15:51.640 align:middle line:84%
is going to be the
paradigm breaker

00:15:51.640 --> 00:15:53.770 align:middle line:90%
for the scientific worldview.

00:15:53.770 --> 00:15:55.810 align:middle line:84%
Because science, as you
say, is leaving it out,

00:15:55.810 --> 00:15:57.018 align:middle line:90%
leaving it out at the moment.

00:15:57.018 --> 00:16:00.310 align:middle line:84%
>> It's kind of surprising that
it ever got to this point where

00:16:00.310 --> 00:16:03.383 align:middle line:84%
scientists had become so
alienated from something

00:16:03.383 --> 00:16:05.050 align:middle line:84%
as basic as consciousness
and free will.

00:16:05.050 --> 00:16:07.540 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, in a way, that
probably goes back to Descartes.

00:16:07.540 --> 00:16:09.490 align:middle line:84%
Because what Descartes
did was he said,

00:16:09.490 --> 00:16:13.090 align:middle line:84%
let's divide the world up
into this res extensa--

00:16:13.090 --> 00:16:17.003 align:middle line:84%
that's Latin for meaning
things with extension in space.

00:16:17.003 --> 00:16:17.920 align:middle line:90%
>> Extension in space.

00:16:17.920 --> 00:16:20.920 align:middle line:84%
>> And there's res cogitans,
which is things in the mind.

00:16:20.920 --> 00:16:24.250 align:middle line:84%
And he said in order not
to alienate the Vatican,

00:16:24.250 --> 00:16:26.920 align:middle line:84%
because he'd already seen people
like Bruno burnt at the stake

00:16:26.920 --> 00:16:28.835 align:middle line:84%
for supporting
Copernicus and ideas that

00:16:28.835 --> 00:16:29.835 align:middle line:90%
went against the church.

00:16:29.835 --> 00:16:32.450 align:middle line:84%
He said, we'll leave things
to do with consciousness,

00:16:32.450 --> 00:16:34.670 align:middle line:90%
the mind, to the church.

00:16:34.670 --> 00:16:36.980 align:middle line:84%
And we'll let science
deal with things

00:16:36.980 --> 00:16:40.680 align:middle line:84%
that exist in space and
time, things with extension.

00:16:40.680 --> 00:16:43.310 align:middle line:84%
And so science went ahead
exploring-- if I simplify,

00:16:43.310 --> 00:16:45.260 align:middle line:84%
basically science
went ahead exploring

00:16:45.260 --> 00:16:47.060 align:middle line:84%
the world of
space-time and matter

00:16:47.060 --> 00:16:49.400 align:middle line:90%
and left consciousness aside.

00:16:49.400 --> 00:16:51.760 align:middle line:84%
And consciousness moved--
the philosophers started

00:16:51.760 --> 00:16:52.760 align:middle line:90%
exploring consciousness.

00:16:52.760 --> 00:16:54.260 align:middle line:84%
There became many
great philosophers

00:16:54.260 --> 00:16:56.468 align:middle line:84%
who looked into that, and
we have the whole tradition

00:16:56.468 --> 00:16:58.130 align:middle line:84%
of European philosophy,
a lot of which

00:16:58.130 --> 00:16:59.990 align:middle line:90%
was exploring consciousness.

00:16:59.990 --> 00:17:02.040 align:middle line:84%
And then it moved
into psychology.

00:17:02.040 --> 00:17:05.089 align:middle line:10%
And now today we're seeing that
whole trend, the exploration

00:17:05.089 --> 00:17:08.540 align:middle line:10%
of consciousness, coming to a
point where we're saying we now

00:17:08.540 --> 00:17:12.440 align:middle line:10%
have to go back and re-look
at our scientific worldview

00:17:12.440 --> 00:17:14.339 align:middle line:10%
and perhaps bring
them back together.

00:17:14.339 --> 00:17:15.950 align:middle line:10%
That split that
Descartes made, it's

00:17:15.950 --> 00:17:18.560 align:middle line:10%
now time to join the
two back together again,

00:17:18.560 --> 00:17:20.810 align:middle line:10%
and so bring the world
of matter together

00:17:20.810 --> 00:17:21.890 align:middle line:10%
with the world of spirit.

00:17:21.890 --> 00:17:24.349 align:middle line:84%
>> You write quite a bit
about the explorations

00:17:24.349 --> 00:17:27.369 align:middle line:84%
into consciousness of the
philosopher Immanuel Kant.

00:17:27.369 --> 00:17:28.660 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:17:28.660 --> 00:17:31.970 align:middle line:84%
Well, Immanuel Kant, I think,
is probably as important in this

00:17:31.970 --> 00:17:33.140 align:middle line:90%
as Copernicus was.

00:17:33.140 --> 00:17:36.260 align:middle line:84%
In fact, Kant himself,
without being arrogant,

00:17:36.260 --> 00:17:39.680 align:middle line:84%
he suggested his ideas were
going to trigger a Copernican

00:17:39.680 --> 00:17:41.630 align:middle line:90%
revolution in philosophy.

00:17:41.630 --> 00:17:45.830 align:middle line:84%
And it took Copernicus 150 years
before his ideas were proven.

00:17:45.830 --> 00:17:47.570 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's
the same with Kant.

00:17:47.570 --> 00:17:50.360 align:middle line:84%
It's only 200 years ago
that Kant was writing.

00:17:50.360 --> 00:17:52.160 align:middle line:84%
And what Kant said,
which I think is--

00:17:52.160 --> 00:17:54.770 align:middle line:84%
he said many things, but I
think the crucial thing here,

00:17:54.770 --> 00:17:57.690 align:middle line:84%
he said there are,
again, two worlds.

00:17:57.690 --> 00:17:59.820 align:middle line:84%
There is the world
we experience,

00:17:59.820 --> 00:18:02.540 align:middle line:84%
which is the phenomena that
arise in our experience.

00:18:02.540 --> 00:18:05.150 align:middle line:84%
And there is the world out
there, which gives rise to it.

00:18:05.150 --> 00:18:07.190 align:middle line:90%
So there is this table.

00:18:07.190 --> 00:18:11.210 align:middle line:84%
But he said all we ever
know of this table is

00:18:11.210 --> 00:18:15.800 align:middle line:84%
what we experience, is the forms
that arise in consciousness.

00:18:15.800 --> 00:18:18.080 align:middle line:84%
When I see there's
a blue color here,

00:18:18.080 --> 00:18:20.210 align:middle line:84%
he would say there's
no blue out there.

00:18:20.210 --> 00:18:22.370 align:middle line:84%
And he didn't even know
about modern physics.

00:18:22.370 --> 00:18:24.860 align:middle line:10%
The blue is purely
a quality which

00:18:24.860 --> 00:18:27.020 align:middle line:10%
arises in consciousness
in response

00:18:27.020 --> 00:18:29.780 align:middle line:10%
to a particular frequency
of vibration of light.

00:18:29.780 --> 00:18:32.510 align:middle line:10%
But there's no blue
in the physical world.

00:18:32.510 --> 00:18:34.160 align:middle line:10%
There's just a
frequency of vibration.

00:18:34.160 --> 00:18:37.460 align:middle line:10%
>> We could even argue from
the point of view of pure

00:18:37.460 --> 00:18:39.410 align:middle line:10%
physicality, there's
nothing solid here.

00:18:39.410 --> 00:18:44.840 align:middle line:10%
>> No, this is
99.9999999% empty space.

00:18:44.840 --> 00:18:49.007 align:middle line:84%
An atom is like a pea in the
middle of the football stadium

00:18:49.007 --> 00:18:50.840 align:middle line:84%
with other peas revolving
around the stands.

00:18:50.840 --> 00:18:52.370 align:middle line:90%
There's that much empty space.

00:18:52.370 --> 00:18:55.100 align:middle line:84%
But because of electromagnetic
forces and the way

00:18:55.100 --> 00:18:58.760 align:middle line:84%
atoms are bound together,
the empty space of my hand

00:18:58.760 --> 00:19:01.230 align:middle line:84%
will not pass through the
empty space of the table.

00:19:01.230 --> 00:19:04.370 align:middle line:84%
And so I have the
appearance of solidness.

00:19:04.370 --> 00:19:07.730 align:middle line:84%
And that's what solidness is,
is the fact that these things

00:19:07.730 --> 00:19:09.210 align:middle line:90%
won't permeate each other.

00:19:09.210 --> 00:19:11.070 align:middle line:84%
And so we think of them
as physically solid,

00:19:11.070 --> 00:19:11.870 align:middle line:90%
but they're not.

00:19:11.870 --> 00:19:15.613 align:middle line:84%
That's just part of the model
we create in our experience.

00:19:15.613 --> 00:19:17.780 align:middle line:84%
>> Which would be consistent
with Kant's philosophy.

00:19:17.780 --> 00:19:18.350 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly.

00:19:18.350 --> 00:19:19.150 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:19:19.150 --> 00:19:20.840 align:middle line:84%
And so Kant was
saying all we ever

00:19:20.840 --> 00:19:24.170 align:middle line:84%
know is what arises in
consciousness, which is really,

00:19:24.170 --> 00:19:27.080 align:middle line:84%
I think, what a lot of the
great old Eastern philosophers

00:19:27.080 --> 00:19:28.550 align:middle line:84%
are saying, that
all we ever know

00:19:28.550 --> 00:19:32.000 align:middle line:84%
is consciousness and the
arisings in consciousness.

00:19:32.000 --> 00:19:35.720 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's what
many yogis and great saints

00:19:35.720 --> 00:19:39.800 align:middle line:84%
have come to experience through
years and years of meditation,

00:19:39.800 --> 00:19:41.990 align:middle line:84%
of exploration of their
own consciousness.

00:19:41.990 --> 00:19:44.570 align:middle line:84%
They've come to
experience that everything

00:19:44.570 --> 00:19:46.040 align:middle line:90%
is an arising in the mind.

00:19:46.040 --> 00:19:49.610 align:middle line:84%
Everything they know is an
arising in consciousness.

00:19:49.610 --> 00:19:51.802 align:middle line:84%
And in that, I think there
is an incredible freedom.

00:19:51.802 --> 00:19:54.260 align:middle line:84%
That's what they talk about,
is that freedom from thinking,

00:19:54.260 --> 00:19:56.960 align:middle line:84%
that I am at the
mercy of the world,

00:19:56.960 --> 00:20:01.760 align:middle line:84%
as well as, I am continually
the author of my own experience.

00:20:01.760 --> 00:20:05.000 align:middle line:84%
>> In that sense, one might say
that all of our so-called hard

00:20:05.000 --> 00:20:08.630 align:middle line:84%
sciences-- physics,
chemistry, biology--

00:20:08.630 --> 00:20:11.910 align:middle line:84%
are descriptions of
our consciousness.

00:20:11.910 --> 00:20:12.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly.

00:20:12.710 --> 00:20:15.980 align:middle line:84%
Well, what they are is they
are taking our consciousness

00:20:15.980 --> 00:20:18.620 align:middle line:84%
and then from that,
trying to arrive

00:20:18.620 --> 00:20:21.900 align:middle line:84%
at a description of
the external world.

00:20:21.900 --> 00:20:23.990 align:middle line:84%
And what we arrive
at is various models.

00:20:23.990 --> 00:20:26.960 align:middle line:84%
And models are just
ideas in consciousness.

00:20:26.960 --> 00:20:29.810 align:middle line:84%
And an electron is a model
that human consciousness

00:20:29.810 --> 00:20:32.730 align:middle line:84%
has invented to describe
certain experiences

00:20:32.730 --> 00:20:33.950 align:middle line:90%
and certain experiments.

00:20:33.950 --> 00:20:35.353 align:middle line:90%
No one's ever seen an electron.

00:20:35.353 --> 00:20:36.770 align:middle line:84%
And what we know
an electron, it's

00:20:36.770 --> 00:20:38.900 align:middle line:84%
nothing like we
think it might be.

00:20:38.900 --> 00:20:41.150 align:middle line:84%
It's certainly not
a solid particle.

00:20:41.150 --> 00:20:42.410 align:middle line:90%
It's just a model.

00:20:42.410 --> 00:20:44.840 align:middle line:84%
And you could say all
of science is an attempt

00:20:44.840 --> 00:20:47.550 align:middle line:84%
to take that data of
consciousness, that

00:20:47.550 --> 00:20:50.780 align:middle line:84%
arise in consciousness,
and from that form

00:20:50.780 --> 00:20:54.920 align:middle line:84%
maps of what that underlying
reality out there is actually

00:20:54.920 --> 00:20:55.720 align:middle line:90%
like.

00:20:55.720 --> 00:20:58.670 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, from the point of
view of Eastern mysticism,

00:20:58.670 --> 00:21:03.560 align:middle line:84%
consciousness is sort
of a pure empty field.

00:21:03.560 --> 00:21:06.050 align:middle line:84%
What we experience
within that field,

00:21:06.050 --> 00:21:09.500 align:middle line:84%
the objects of consciousness,
are conditioned certainly

00:21:09.500 --> 00:21:11.570 align:middle line:90%
by our biological system.

00:21:11.570 --> 00:21:12.500 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:21:12.500 --> 00:21:14.880 align:middle line:10%
Well, consciousness--
there's pure consciousness,

00:21:14.880 --> 00:21:18.530 align:middle line:10%
which is consciousness
before it takes on form.

00:21:18.530 --> 00:21:20.510 align:middle line:10%
And an analogy I often
think of for that

00:21:20.510 --> 00:21:22.550 align:middle line:10%
is like if you've
got a film projector,

00:21:22.550 --> 00:21:24.650 align:middle line:10%
you've got white
light behind the film.

00:21:24.650 --> 00:21:26.300 align:middle line:10%
That is like the
pure light, which

00:21:26.300 --> 00:21:28.970 align:middle line:10%
is the same for every
single film projector.

00:21:28.970 --> 00:21:32.380 align:middle line:84%
That light shines through
the film onto the screen,

00:21:32.380 --> 00:21:34.370 align:middle line:84%
and it takes on the
colors of the film,

00:21:34.370 --> 00:21:36.920 align:middle line:84%
and you get a particular
image forming.

00:21:36.920 --> 00:21:39.470 align:middle line:84%
But you'd have to take the
film out completely just

00:21:39.470 --> 00:21:40.745 align:middle line:90%
to see the white light.

00:21:40.745 --> 00:21:42.620 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's the
same with consciousness.

00:21:42.620 --> 00:21:44.600 align:middle line:84%
The consciousness, my
consciousness right

00:21:44.600 --> 00:21:47.300 align:middle line:84%
now is taking on all these
forms I'm experiencing

00:21:47.300 --> 00:21:51.160 align:middle line:84%
of you and the studio and also
the thoughts and feelings that

00:21:51.160 --> 00:21:51.960 align:middle line:90%
are inside me.

00:21:51.960 --> 00:21:53.840 align:middle line:90%
It's taking on all these forms.

00:21:53.840 --> 00:21:57.500 align:middle line:10%
But if I were to stop
and become very quiet

00:21:57.500 --> 00:21:59.510 align:middle line:10%
and go into a deep
state of meditation

00:21:59.510 --> 00:22:02.300 align:middle line:10%
so that the mind becomes
still and I'm not experiencing

00:22:02.300 --> 00:22:04.490 align:middle line:10%
the world anymore, then you
can come back to a state

00:22:04.490 --> 00:22:07.880 align:middle line:10%
where you are just that
pure light of consciousness

00:22:07.880 --> 00:22:11.870 align:middle line:10%
before it takes on all
these multitudinous forms.

00:22:11.870 --> 00:22:14.420 align:middle line:84%
>> It's interesting, Peter, that
you mentioned the pure light

00:22:14.420 --> 00:22:16.220 align:middle line:90%
